Wash and dry produce.

In a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings), combine @pho stock concentrate{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, half the @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and @water{4%cups} (8 cups water for 4) over medium-high heat. Cover and bring to a boil.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz}, remaining hoisin, @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @pepper{}. Form pork mixture into 10-12 1-inch meatballs (20-24 meatballs for 4). TIP: If broth reaches a boil before meatballs are ready, reduce heat to low. Before adding meatballs, increase heat to medium high and return broth to a boil.

Once broth is boiling, carefully add meatballs to #pot{}. Cover and cook until meatballs are cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%oz} and @ramen noodles{4.5%oz} to pot. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies and noodles are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide ramen between #bowls{}. Drizzle with as much @sriracha{1%tsp} as you like. Serve.